This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a system for semantic segmentation of 3D maps using RGB-D data. It also involves deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision research. Additionally, the paper is likely to belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it discusses the application of the proposed system in intelligent robotics. Other possible sub-categories include machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL) as the proposed system involves deep learning techniques and semantic labelling of 3D maps.
